Description:
    Installs RailsJsLogger to forward JavaScript console output to Rails logs.

Example:
    rails generate rails_js_logger:install

    This will create:
        config/initializers/rails_js_logger.rb

    And modify:
        config/routes.rb (mounts the engine)
        config/importmap.rb (if using importmap-rails)
        app/javascript/application.js (if using importmap-rails)

Configuration:
    After installation, customize config/initializers/rails_js_logger.rb:

        RailsJsLogger.enabled = true
        RailsJsLogger.log_level = :debug
        RailsJsLogger.tag = "JS"
        RailsJsLogger.sample_rate = 1.0
        RailsJsLogger.max_payload_size = 100_000
